article.headline: Radford 65, Presbyterian 55
article.story: CLINTON, S.C. -- Joey Lynch-Flohr scored 15 points on 6-of-11 shooting to lead Radford to a 65-55 win over Presbyterian College on Saturday night. Artisom Parakhouski added 14 points and 14 rebounds for the Highlanders (5-9, 2-1 Big South Conference). Amir Johnson chipped in with 13 points. Pierre Miller led the Blue Hose (5-9, 2-1) with 15 points. Josh Johnson added 13 points, three assists and four steals. Chase Holmes finished with 12 points. Radford shot 53.1 percent from the field (26-for-49), including 51.7 percent (15-for-29) in the first half. They held a 36-18 halftime lead. Presbyterian shot only 33.3 percent (7-for-21) in the first half, and shot 43.5 percent for the game (20-for-46). Radford outrebounded the Blue Hose 37-21.
